[[File:Alui-TEA.jpg|thumb|right|250px|The Alui Corridor shared its name with the Alui system (depicted on map) of the Mid Rim.]]
The '''Alui Corridor''' was a [[Hyperspace route/Legends|hyperlane]] that served as a major tourist route.<ref name="AIR">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]''</ref> It shared its name with the [[Alui system/Legends|Alui system]], a part of the [[Mid Rim/Legends|Mid Rim's]] [[Alui sector/Legends|Alui sector]]<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref> that was situated on the [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] route known as the [[Duros Space Run]].<ref name="DurosSpaceRun">''[[The Essential Atlas]]'' places the [[Alui system/Legends|Alui system]] on the [[Hyperspace route/Legends|hyperlane]] {{SW|url=news/essential-atlas-extra-the-knight-errant-gazetter|text=Essential Atlas Extra: The Knight Errant Gazetteer|int=The Knight Errant Gazetteer}} identifies as the [[Duros Space Run]].</ref>

At some point between approximately [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]] and [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]],<ref name="Date Batta">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'' represents a collection of [[in-universe]] reports from "one [[Standard year/Legends|year]] before the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]]," which corresponds to [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]], according to ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''. Furthermore, ''Alliance Intelligence Reports'' states that [[Callow Batta]] began his career as a [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] "about a year ago" and therefore around [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]].</ref> [[Doctor/Legends|Doctor]] [[Callow Batta]], a former [[Professor/Legends|professor]] of governmental and [[Politics/Legends|political]] history at the [[University of Sanbra]] who had turned to [[Pirate/Legends|piracy]] and [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggling]] after he had been fired by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] authorities, carried out multiple raids on [[Starship/Legends|starships]] traveling along the Alui Corridor. Eventually, [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] [[General/Legends|General]] [[Airen Cracken/Legends|Airen Cracken]] submitted a [[Task Force on Alliance Security]] [[SecuriDex]] [[Datafile/Legends|datafile]] on Batta, which noted him as posing a low-level threat to Alliance operatives traveling on the Alui Corridor.<ref name="AIR" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Alui Corridor was mentioned in ''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'', a [[1995]] sourcebook for [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="AIR" />

